<h2>Please read Chapter Three</h2>

<p align="center"><u><i><font size="4">Styles &amp; Style Sheets</font></i></u></p>
<p align="center">Ultimate Style Example. Courtesy of
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.csszengarden.com/">Zen Garden.</a></p>

<font color="purple">
<p align="left"><b>Inline style attribute can be used to apply styles to a single element</b></p>
&lt;h1 style="font-size:500%; color:red;"&gt;Valley Town Hall&lt;/h1&gt;
</p><p>
Common units of measure for font size:
<ul>
<li>px  stands for pixels</li>
<li>pt  stands for points (1/72 of an inch)</li>
<li>%   stands for percent (relative to current value)</li>
<li>em  stands for ems or emphasize (relative to current font size)</li>
</font>
</ul>
</font>

<p align="left"><b>Internal (Embedded) Styles (Contained in the &lt;head&gt; )</b></p>
<p align="left">Used for formatting in a SINGLE web page. </p>
<p align="left">tag:</p>
<p align="left">&lt;style&gt;</p>
<p align="left">&lt;/style&gt;</p>
<p align="left">attributes:</p>
<p align="left">type</p>
<p align="left">generally type=&quot;text/css&quot;</p>
<p align="left">We also need to specify a default style sheet language for the 
whole document. To do so we use a meta tag placed within the &lt;head&gt;.</p>
<p align="left"><b>&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Style-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/css&quot; /&gt;</b></p>
<p align="left">basic style sytax:&nbsp; <b>&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
tag {property : value}&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;/style&gt;</b></p>
<p align="left">Example:</p>
<p align="left">&lt;head&gt;</p>
<p align="left">&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Style-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/css&quot; /&gt;</p>
<p align="left">&lt;title&gt; style example &lt;/title&gt;</p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
h1 {color: #ff00ff}&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;/style&gt;<br>
&lt;/head&gt;</p>
<p align="left">Other properties for various tags: text-align, <font size="4">
font-size</font>, <i>font-style</i>, <font face="Arial Black">font-family</font></p>
<p align="left"><b>Style classes:</b></p>
<p align="left">Class is a type of sub-style </p>
<p align="left">Syntax: <b>tag.classname</b></p>
<p align="left">Example: </p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
h1 {color: #ff00ff}<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
h1.color2 {color : #0000ff}&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;/style&gt;</p>
<p align="left">Then in the body</p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;h1&gt; this is a sample of the new h1 color &lt;/h1&gt;</p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&lt;h1 class=&quot;color2&quot;&gt; this is a sample of h1 color 2 &lt;/h1&gt;</p>
<p align="left"><b>External Style Sheets:</b></p>
<p align="left">An external style sheet is simply a text-only file that contains 
only style definitions. </p>
<p align="left">File is created in notepad and saved with a .css extension.</p>
<p align="left">Linked to html file with a &lt;link&gt; tag in the &lt;head&gt;.</p>
<p align="left"><b>&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;filename.css&quot;&gt;</b></p>
<p align="left">Example of what may be defined in style sheet:</p>
<p align="left"><b>body<br>
{<br>
font-family: Garamond, Times New Roman, Times;<br>
background-color: rgb(51,102,204);<br>
color: rgb(255,255,153);<br>
}<br>
table<br>
{<br>
table-border-color-light: rgb(153,255,204);<br>
table-border-color-dark: rgb(0,0,51); <br>
}<br>
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6<br>
{<br>
font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica;<br>
}<br>
h1<br>
{<br>
color: #ff00FF;<br>
}<br>
h2<br>
{<br>
color: #ff3300; <br>
}<br>
h3<br>
{<br>
color: rgb(0,255,204); <br>
}<br>
h4<br>
{<br>
color: rgb(255,204,0);<br>
}<br>
h5<br>
{<br>
color: rgb(153,255,51);<br>
}<br>
h6<br>
{<br>
color: rgb(0,255,204);<br>
}</b><br>
&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>

<p><font color="purple">
<b>The sequence in which styles are applied</b>
<ul>
<li>Styles from an external style sheet</li>
<li>Embedded styles in head section</li>
<li>Inline styles</li>
<li>The rule applied last overrides the earlier rules</li>
</ul>
</font>

<br><br>
<p><font color="purple">
<p><b>Cascading rules</b>
</p><p>
The term "Cascading Style Sheets" refers to the fact that
more than one style sheet can be applied to a single web page.  If two or more rules for the same property are
applied to the same element, the "cascade order"
determines which rule takes precedence:
!important rules precede normal rules precede default rules.
If rules have the same
cascade order, the last rule applied overrides the other
rules.
</p>
<p>
<br><br>

</font>
<strong><font color=red>Notes: To make sure the style sheet work for older browsers,
you need to observe the following:
<br><br>
(1) On each page,
add the following two cryptic lines BEFORE the &lt;html&gt; tag:<br>
<ul> &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot;?&gt; <br> &lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 
        Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www/w3/org/TR/xhtml/11/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;</ul> 
<br>
(2) There must be NO SPACE between : and the attribute value
</font></strong>
